🧠 Problem Summary (In Your Words)
You have n bullets → fixed order
Each bullet deals damage a[i]
Enemy health = h
After firing all n bullets → reload takes k seconds
You can do at most 1 swap before starting

👉 Goal: Min time to kill enemy

🔥 Key Observations (MOST IMPORTANT)
1. Full magazine cycles are FIXED

Let:

sum = total damage of one magazine

Then:

cycles = h / sum
remaining = h % sum

👉 You must use at least cycles full magazines

2. Swap DOES NOT affect full cycles

💡 Why?

Because:

sum of array remains same after swap

👉 So:

Total damage per magazine = SAME
Time per magazine = SAME

✅ Swap only affects LAST magazine

⚡ Time Calculation
Case 1: Exact kill
remaining == 0

Then:

time = cycles * n + (cycles - 1) * k

👉 Last reload not needed

Case 2: Remaining > 0
time = cycles * n + cycles * k

👉 Now we need extra bullets from last magazine

🎯 Core Problem Reduced To:

Find minimum i (1 ≤ i ≤ n)
such that we can deal ≥ remaining damage using first i bullets
(with at most one swap)

🔄 Swap Strategy (CRITICAL INSIGHT)

For a fixed i:

👉 Best swap is:

(min in prefix [0..i]) ↔ (max in suffix [i+1..n-1])
🤔 Why this works?

We want to:

REMOVE smallest damage from prefix
ADD largest possible damage from suffix

👉 Maximizes prefix sum → best chance to kill early

📊 Precomputations
1. Prefix Sum
pref[i] = sum of a[0..i]
2. Prefix Minimum
pref_min[i] = min(a[0..i])
3. Suffix Maximum
suff_max[i] = max(a[i..n-1])
🧪 For Each i (0-based)
Case 1: No swap
damage = pref[i]
Case 2: With swap

Only if:

i + 1 < n AND pref_min[i] < suff_max[i+1]

Then:

damage = pref[i] - pref_min[i] + suff_max[i+1]
✅ Condition
if damage ≥ remaining
    answer = i + 1

Take minimum i

⛔ Why NOT Binary Search?

Because:

prefix sum after swap is NOT monotonic

👉 So:

i=2 might work
i=3 might NOT
i=4 might work

❌ Not monotonic → ❌ No binary search

🧾 Final Algorithm
Step-by-step:
Compute sum
Compute:
cycles = h / sum
remaining = h % sum
If remaining == 0 → return directly
Precompute:
prefix sum
prefix min
suffix max
Loop i = 0 → n-1
Try:
no swap
swap
Find smallest i
Return:
time + (i + 1)
⏱ Complexity
O(n) per test case
